00:00:24.130 --> 00:00:29.764
Let see what are ingredients we require to prepare Kache Aam ki chutney.

00:00:30.476 --> 00:00:32.389
Raw mango - 1

00:00:32.774 --> 00:00:37.298
Chopped coriander - 2 cups

00:00:37.993 --> 00:00:41.390
Mint leaves - 1/2 cup

00:00:41.718 --> 00:00:43.774
Heeng (Asafoetida) - 2 pinches

00:00:44.270 --> 00:00:48.127
Salt - 1/2 tsp or according to taste

00:00:48.560 --> 00:00:51.314
Black salt - 1/2 tsp

00:00:51.865 --> 00:00:54.199
Roasted Jeera - 1 tsp

00:00:54.439 --> 00:00:56.320
Ginger - A piece of 1 inch

00:00:56.671 --> 00:00:58.703
Green chilli - 3 to 4

00:00:59.397 --> 00:01:08.545
Peel the raw mango first to prepare the chutney of raw mango.

00:01:15.477 --> 00:01:18.382
Take out its pulp.

00:01:23.684 --> 00:01:25.922
Make the small pieces of pulp.

00:01:29.778 --> 00:01:34.278
We have already prepared coriander and mint leaves.

00:01:35.252 --> 00:01:44.097
Put pieces of raw mango, coriander and mint leaves.

00:01:46.788 --> 00:01:50.987
Make smaller pieces of the piece of ginger.

00:01:58.722 --> 00:02:10.303
Also add green chilli, ginger, roasted jeera, black salt, common salt and Heeng.

00:02:12.879 --> 00:02:14.387
Add half cup water in it.

00:02:18.758 --> 00:02:21.353
Grind the chutney to make it a fine paste.

00:02:37.262 --> 00:02:40.658
The fine paste of chutney is now prepared.

00:02:43.784 --> 00:02:48.324
The mouth-watering and aromatic chutney is now ready.

00:02:48.702 --> 00:02:55.557
You should prepare this chutney whenever you are preparing Samosa, Kachori or Pakora.

00:02:58.521 --> 00:03:03.674
You can prepare this chutney at home and can be taken with meals.

00:03:04.282 --> 00:03:08.750
We can use for 7 days when kept in refrigerator.

